<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 16 at 3:59PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...THE SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING FOR EAST CENTRAL BROADWATER AND
SOUTHEASTERN MEAGHER COUNTIES WILL EXPIRE AT 400 PM MDT...
The storm which prompted the warning has weakened below severe
limits, and no longer poses an immediate threat to life or property.
Therefore, the warning will be allowed to expire.  Pea sized hail
and wind gusts to around 50 mph are still possible with this
thunderstorm it continues across southeast Meagher county through
430 PM.</description>
